songs.title: You Don’t Know My Name (Interlude)
songs.lyrics:
[Intro: Kanye West]
DJ, offbeat
Remember when I was off-earth
The trip
Yeah, um
She look, she look good as a motherfucker
But I can't remember her name
I can’t remember her name for nothing
Look, you took her number down right?
You took her number down right?
Know what? I'm just gonna go ahead and call this girl
Hello, what's up? It’s Kanye
Nah it's really me
You know who I am?
I don't usually do this but
I'm only going to be in town for one night
I want to know if you want to come by the room or something
Would that be cool?
Ok, cool, cool
Come around
Ok, ok let me take your coat
You think I'm gonna massage or something
Ok, ok, that's what I thought
I'm trying to say, I'm trying to say what’s up
You know, I’m saying, um
Wait a second, you came too honey
It's that time of the month
Oh man
Will you tell me
I ain’t playing, this is what I want you to say
But we got to, we got to put down something
Um, um, all we ask is that we pay what we done
It's like

[Chorus: Kanye West & John Legend]
But I still don't know your name girl
Wherever we go, she be going home
I swear it feels like Wooo, ooh, ooh
And I still don't know your name
Falling down, I been on, she be all alone
